- "I've always had a great relationship with the press. It's very simple — whatever they write about you, keep them interested." — documented
- "Bad publicity is sometimes better than no publicity at all." — documented

### On positive thinking (Peale influence)
- "I never think of the negative." — multiple documented instances
- "Part of the beauty of me is that I am very rich." — 2011 interview

### Rally signature phrases
- "Make America Great Again" (MAGA) — from 1987 book; campaign slogan 2016, 2024
- "You're fired!" — *The Apprentice*, 2004-2015
- "Build the wall!" — 2015-present campaign rallies
- "Drain the swamp!" — 2016 campaign slogan
- "America First" — foreign policy doctrine, both terms
- "Fake news!" — coined/popularized 2016; applied to unfavorable media
- "Witch hunt!" — applied to all legal/investigative proceedings against him
- "The greatest [X] in the history of our country" — universal superlative formula

